# New Package

## Arguments
- `name`: Package name (kebab-case, e.g., `shared-types`)
- `type`: `node` | `go`

## Steps

### 1. Create Package Files
{{ if .Computed.HasNode }}
**Node.js** (`packages/node/{name}/`):
- `package.json` with `{{ .Computed.PrimaryScope }}/{name}` scope
- `tsconfig.json` extending base config
- `tsconfig.build.json` for production builds
- `vitest.config.ts`
- `src/index.ts` (barrel export)
- `src/types.ts` (initial types)
{{ end }}
{{ if .Computed.HasGo }}
**Go** (`packages/go/{name}/`):
- `go.mod` with module path
- `{name}.go` with package declaration
{{ end }}

### 2. Register in Workspace
{{ if .Computed.HasNode }}- Package is auto-discovered by {{ .Project.Spec.Monorepo.PackageManager }} workspaces{{ end }}
{{ if .Computed.HasGo }}- Add to `go.work`: `use ./packages/go/{name}`{{ end }}

### 3. Build
{{ if .Computed.HasNode }}- Run `{{ .Project.Spec.Monorepo.PackageManager }} install`
- Run `{{ .Project.Spec.Monorepo.PackageManager }} nx build {name}`{{ end }}
{{ if .Computed.HasGo }}- Run `go work sync && go mod tidy`{{ end }}

## Checklist
- [ ] Package files created
- [ ] Registered in workspace
- [ ] Builds successfully
- [ ] Can be imported by services
